    {
      "id": "OF4fQ69S9QNL7Qbo",
      "questionNumber": 7,
      "questionText": "An unknown alcohol is treated with the “Lucas reagent” to determine whether the alcohol is primary,\nsecondary or tertiary. Which alcohol reacts fastest and by what mechanism: ",
      "options": [
        "tertiary alcohol by S<sub>N</sub>1",
        "secondary alcohol by S<sub>N</sub>2",
        "tertiary alcohol by S<sub>N</sub>2",
        "secondary alcohol by S<sub>N</sub>1 "
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "properties-preparation-and-uses-of-alcohols",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Tertiary alcohols reacts fastest with lucas reagnet as the rate of reaction is directly proportional to the stability of carbocation formed in the reaction. Since most stable $${3^ \\circ }$$ carbocation is formed in the reaction hence it will react fastest further tetriary alcohols appears to react by $${S_N}1$$ mechanism.\n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/fHWuWONlEt2DaP0iH/rOSfnYYSzLV5kF24XQNhyOEHgHUu3/OZ7xqcfqGGcpzZfrhBkSmO/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2013 (Offline) Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 172 English Explanation\"> ",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "ml80adzk",
      "questionNumber": 8,
      "questionText": "<p>The reactions which produce alcohol as the product are :</p>\n<p>A. $\\mathrm{CH}_4 + \\mathrm{O}_2 \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{Mo}_2\\mathrm{O}_3,\\ \\Delta} $</p>\n<p>B. $2\\mathrm{CH}_3\\mathrm{CH}_3 + 3\\mathrm{O}_2 \\xrightarrow{(\\mathrm{CH}_3\\mathrm{COO})_2\\mathrm{Mn},\\ \\Delta} $</p>\n<p>C. $(\\mathrm{CH}_3)_3\\mathrm{CH} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{KMnO}_4} $</p>\n<p>D. $ 2\\mathrm{CH}_4 + \\mathrm{O}_2 \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{Cu}/523\\ \\mathrm{K}/100 \\ \\mathrm{atm}.} $</p>\n<p>E. $\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{KMnO}_4/\\mathrm{H}^+} $ </p>\n<p>Choose the <b>correct</b> answer from the options given below :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>B, D and E Only</p>",
        "<p>A and D Only</p>",
        "<p>A, C and E Only</p>",
        "<p>C and D Only</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 3,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "properties-preparation-and-uses-of-alcohols",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>$$ \\text { Reaction given Alcohol } $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\text { (A) } \\mathrm{CH}_4+\\mathrm{O}_2 \\xrightarrow[\\Delta]{\\mathrm{Mo}_2 \\mathrm{O}_3} \\mathrm{HCHO} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\text { (B) } 2 \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_3+3 \\mathrm{O}_2 \\xrightarrow[\\Delta]{\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COO}\\right)_2 \\mathrm{Mn}} \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOH} $$</p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 28th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 14 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mlbafdv0/d78a56a5-c7c7-4919-9df0-2047cbbe6f15/58d5d2c0-0393-11f1-aba0-254ecb2a9d9c/file-jaoe38c1mlbafdv1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mlbafdv0/d78a56a5-c7c7-4919-9df0-2047cbbe6f15/58d5d2c0-0393-11f1-aba0-254ecb2a9d9c/file-jaoe38c1mlbafdv1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\text { (D) } 2 \\mathrm{CH}_4+\\mathrm{O}_2 \\xrightarrow[523 \\mathrm{~K}, 100 \\text { atm }]{\\mathrm{Cu}} \\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{OH} $$</p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 28th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 14 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mlbafeu5/f5b654f7-9035-4323-b95d-28cbf4d3ec41/5996d8d0-0393-11f1-aba0-254ecb2a9d9c/file-jaoe38c1mlbafeu6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mlbafeu5/f5b654f7-9035-4323-b95d-28cbf4d3ec41/5996d8d0-0393-11f1-aba0-254ecb2a9d9c/file-jaoe38c1mlbafeu6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\text { And. } \\rightarrow \\quad C, D $$</p>",
